st drug possession arrest — or a second one — means hitting bottom. It can be a difficult time. Clients can benefit by addressing issues of drug abuse and addiction. We help refer clients to treatment programs. We recommend chemical dependency evaluations and counseling.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group for a Free Initial Consultation</h3>\r\nTo talk about your drug possession arrest with an attorney at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas law office at [number type=\"1\"]. We answer our phones 24 hours a day, 7 days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when an arrest has put your freedom at stake.', 'Drug Crimes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '329-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-23 10:51:09', '2013-10-23 10:51:09', '', '329', 'http://brentbowen.com/329-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('333', '1', '2013-10-23 10:51:48', '2013-10-23 10:51:48', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Legal Representation After an Arrest for a Theft Crime</h2>\r\nWhether it resulted from an error in judgment, a false accusation or another situation entirely, an arrest for a theft crime should be taken seriously. And the first step to a serious criminal defense is to work with a knowledgeable and experienced attorney.\r\n\r\nOur criminal defense lawyer — Brent Bowen — is a former Denton County assistant district attorney who knows the law and who focuses on providing strong and effective criminal defense.\r\n\r\nOur Denton, Texas, law firm handles a broad range of felony and misdemeanor theft crimes in Texas state courts. Regardless of the allegations you face, we can talk openly with you about building a strong criminal defense:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Robbery and aggravated robbery</li>\r\n	<li>Burglary</li>\r\n	<li>Shoplifting</li>\r\n	<li>Embezzlement / employee theft</li>\r\n	<li>Auto theft</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Search and Seizure Issues</h3>\r\nEach arrest is unique, but most arrests for theft crimes involve some issues related to search and seizure. WhenBowen Law Group handles your case, we always check to make sure that police followed the letter of the law.\r\n\r\nThe law on search and seizure is constantly changing as existing laws are applied in new situations. The attorneys at Bowen Law Group stay current on the law so that we can offer quality representation to our clients.\r\n\r\nOur law firm philosophy is based on understanding our clients as people, not just as cases. Other issues, like financial hardship, drug or alcohol dependence, are often behind an arrest for a theft crime. As attorneys and counselors, we help you get the support you need for those issues — in addition to providing a strong and effective criminal defense in Texas courts.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\nTo talk about your criminal defense with an attorney at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when you need them most.', 'Theft, Burglary, Robbery', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '330-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-23 10:51:48', '2013-10-23 10:51:48', '', '330', 'http://brentbowen.com/330-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('334', '1', '2013-10-23 10:52:42', '2013-10-23 10:52:42', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Criminal Defense for Assault Allegations</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/phikvDuso2A?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\nWhen allegations of violence lead to an arrest, the situation is often difficult and emotional. At Bowen Law Group, in Denton, Texas, we offer confidential and non-judgmental criminal defense that helps you achieve positive results in Texas state courts.\r\n\r\nAt Bowen Law Group, criminal defense lawyer Brent Bowen is a former Denton County assistant district attorney who is respected by prosecutors. Brent has a reputation for straight talk and effective action in Texas state courts.\r\n<h3>Representing People Accused of Violent Crimes in Texas State Courts</h3>\r\nWe represent people accused of a wide range of violent crimes, including assault, sexual assault and other violent conduct. We also handle family law disputes, like assault allegations related to domestic violence or allegations of child abuse made by Child Protective Services (CPS). Attorney Chrysandra Bowen handles these family issues with the attention and sensitivity they deserve, using her counseling background.\r\n\r\nWhen we take your assault case, we begin exploring all your options. Sometimes self defense is an effective explanation for your actions. Other times, witnesses are not credible. Regardless of the situation, our aim is to achieve positive results. However, there are times when the clients would benefit from anger management or family counseling.\r\n\r\nTexas law has changed. Now homeowners have no duty to retreat before defending themselves against dangerous intruders in their own homes. However, because each situation is unique, it is best to talk about your situation with an experienced lawyer.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\nTo talk about the assault allegations you face with an attorney at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when you need them most.', 'Assault', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '331-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-23 10:52:42', '2013-10-23 10:52:42', '', '331', 'http://brentbowen.com/331-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('336', '1', '2013-10-23 10:53:45', '2013-10-23 10:53:45', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Denton, Texas, Attorney for Juvenile Law Issues</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/ckivCodlNas?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nKids and teens are not adults, and — unless the allegations are especially serious — Texas law does not treat them that way. In Texas, juvenile cases are civil rather than criminal in nature.\r\n\r\nIn order to achieve results, it is important to work with a lawyer who knows Texas juvenile law. At Bowen Law Group, attorney Brent Bowen is a former Denton County assistant district attorney who is experienced in defending young people in juvenile matters.\r\n\r\nOur Denton, Texas, law firm handles a wide range of offenses under Texas juvenile law:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Minor in possession</li>\r\n	<li>Drug crimes</li>\r\n	<li>Assault</li>\r\n	<li>Sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Robbery</li>\r\n	<li>Shoplifting</li>\r\n	<li>Burglary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition to representing offenders in juvenile court, we also handle related administrative matters, like suspensions and expulsions from Texas schools. We also talk to our clients about sealing juvenile records, or expunction and non-disclosure of criminal records after an offense.\r\n<h3>Quick Action for Juvenile Detention Hearings</h3>\r\nInstead of being arrested, minors are “detained” or “taken into custody.” Under Texas law, if a juvenile is detained, he or she must be held in a special facility separate from adult violators. The law requires that a detention hearing be held before a judge — usually the day after the child was taken into custody. Only a judge after a detention hearing can release a juvenile to a parent, guardian or custodian.\r\n\r\nAt Bowen Law Group, we understand the stress and worry families feel when a child has been taken into custody. We have a 24-hour, seven-day-a-week phone line so that we can respond quickly to juvenile law issues — especially when your family needs it most.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\nTo talk with an attorney at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns.', ' Juvenile Law', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'juvenile-law', '', '', '2013-10-30 09:31:11', '2013-10-30 09:31:11', '', '0', 'http://brentbowen.com/?page_id=336', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('337', '1', '2013-10-23 10:54:30', '2013-10-23 10:54:30', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Sealing Your Texas Criminal Records</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/i43kB2sjjwk?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nSometimes a criminal record can limit your future possibilities. It can keep you from getting the right job, or from moving in to the right apartment. But a knowledgeable attorney can help you take action under Texas law, sealing these records and protecting your future.\r\n\r\nAt Bowen Law Group, located in Denton, Texas, we help clients with two different methods of criminal record expungement: expunction and nondisclosure. Depending on the circumstances surrounding your detention, arrest or conviction, either one might be the right fit for you.\r\n<h3>What is the Difference Between Expunction and Non-Disclosure?</h3>\r\n<strong>Expunction:</strong> Expunction orders essentially erase all records of the offense — arrest records, court records and criminal history record information — from your criminal record. Expunction is only granted in certain circumstances, however. These include when a criminal case was dismissed or when you were found not guilty after a criminal trial. People who are not eligible for expunction may still be eligible for non-disclosure.\r\n\r\n<strong>Non-disclosure:</strong> When a petition for non-disclosure is granted, criminal justice agencies are prohibited from giving information about the offense to the public. Usually, non-disclosure is granted in certain circumstances, like when you have successfully completed a deferred adjudication. For many offenses, there is a waiting period before you can file a petition for non-disclosure. Some offenses are eligible for non-disclosure immediately.\r\n\r\nTexas law also provides for the sealing of juvenile records. If your juvenile records are ordered sealed by the court, they are removed from the criminal history database. At Bowen Law Group, we can help with this and with other issues of juvenile law.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\nTo talk about expunction or non-disclosure with a lawyer at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when you need them most.', 'Expunction and Non-Disclosure', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'expunction-and-non-disclosure', '', '', '2013-10-30 09:32:52', '2013-10-30 09:32:52', '', '0', 'http://brentbowen.com/?page_id=337', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('338', '1', '2013-10-23 10:54:59', '2013-10-23 10:54:59', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">When You Have Been Accused of a Probation Violation</h2>\r\nThere are many reasons why people are accused of violating probation — a DWI, a failed drug test or UA, failing to pay court-ordered fines or another offense. Often, a lapse in judgment or a false accusation is the reason.\r\n\r\nRegardless of the circumstances involved in your situation, Bowen Law Group can help. As a former Denton County assistant district attorney, Brent Bowen has in-depth knowledge of Texas law on probation violations. He provides strong and effective defenses for people accused of probation violations.\r\n\r\nOur Denton, Texas, law firm handles motions to revoke probation in Texas courts. We also provide representation in defense of motions to adjudicate, for men and women on adjudicated probation — those placed on formal probation without a conviction.\r\n<h3>Understanding Our Clients — Not Just Their Cases</h3>\r\nAt Bowen Law Group, our law firm philosophy is based on understanding clients, not just their cases. This means that we often look beyond the immediate legal issue, like a probation violation, to the things that are really affecting you.\r\n\r\nSometimes this means helping you get the resources you need to manage a drug, alcohol or anger management issue. Regardless of the issues that you face, you can trust Bowen Law Group for non-judgmental and confidential legal representation that gets real results.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\nTo talk about a probation violation or another criminal defense issue with a lawyer at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when you need them most.', 'Probation Violations', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'probation-violations', '', '', '2013-10-30 09:34:11', '2013-10-30 09:34:11', '', '0', 'http://brentbowen.com/?page_id=338', '0', 'page', '', '0');
