INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('383', '1', '2013-10-23 12:06:52', '2013-10-23 12:06:52', 'CHRYSANDRA BOWEN: You will typically find people fighting over child custody in family law cases. That includes visitation, possession, and child support. Behind that, you’re going to find people fighting over other assets, which would mostly be money. How is the money going to be split and any property that they have?\r\n\r\nChild custody can be determined either by status quo, which is what is the situation at the time of separation. Or when you go into court, the court’s going to look more at who’s the primary parent doing the primary roles for the child. The one piece of advice I often give my clients is that they have to push emotions aside. You have to focus on moving on with your life and dividing up your assets. If there are children involved, it’s more important that you focus on their needs than your own.\r\n\r\nThe thing that I enjoy about family law is that I can step into someone’s shoes that is very emotional and not able to focus on the actual legal aspects of a marriage. It’s easy for me to push that aside and negotiate for them for what’s fair. Fair is not always what everyone thinks it is. But it’s what the law will allow you. If you’re experiencing a family law matter, you should hire Bowen Law Group because we understand our clients, not just their cases.', 'Family Law Video Transcript', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'family-law-video-transcript', '', '', '2013-10-23 12:06:52', '2013-10-23 12:06:52', '', '0', 'http://brentbowen.com/?page_id=383', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('384', '1', '2013-10-23 12:07:11', '2013-10-23 12:07:11', 'BRENT BOWEN: At the Bowen Law Group, we handle all types of criminal cases, from traffic tickets, DWIs, drug cases, assaults, anywhere from attempted murder to murder charges.\r\n\r\nI’ve been practicing criminal law for nearly 10 years. I’ve worked in county attorneys’ offices, district attorneys’ offices, as well as being in private practice for a number of years. Working for a district attorney’s office is I believe a benefit to my clients. I understand how things are processed through that office, which sometimes benefits my clients, where I might be able to head off a charge before it’s actually filed with the court.\r\n\r\nThere is no typical client that we deal with here at the Bowen Law Group. It’s important when dealing with a client to understand what’s going on in their lives and not just their criminal case. We try here at Bowen Law Group to get the clients the required counseling they may need or to benefit themselves as well as their case. Clients typically don’t understand the severity of the matter that they’re involved in. The range of punishment for offenses in Texas can be very different, depending on what type of charge they have. It’s important for clients to understand when they’re charged with a crime to immediately contact an attorney. They have certain rights that they need to protect. And they might not understand the criminal justice system.', 'Criminal Law Video Transcript', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'criminal-law-video-transcript', '', '', '2013-10-23 12:07:11', '2013-10-23 12:07:11', '', '0', 'http://brentbowen.com/?page_id=384', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('385', '1', '2013-10-23 12:07:32', '2013-10-23 12:07:32', 'BRENT BOWEN: Our firm practices in the area of criminal and family law. And inside the family-criminal law realm, we also practice juvenile law.\r\n\r\nCriminal and family law can intertwine. A lot of times clients don’t understand what type of lawyer they really need. And sometimes in the family law issue, there may be criminal consequences. So it’s important to have both in one office.\r\n\r\nOur team consists of myself and my wife Cassandra. I handle the bulk of the criminal law cases, while she handles the majority of the family law cases. And we try to take a team approach to each case.\r\n\r\nA lot of clients come in with drug and alcohol problems. And so we try to focus on the client’s problems first and then deal with their cases second. My wife Cassandra Bowen does have a background in alcohol and drug counseling, which is very helpful when you deal with clients who have alcohol and drug dependency issues.\r\n\r\nAs a fourth generation attorney, it’s important to stay current on the law. The laws change every year. And we go continue with education to focus our practice in the appropriate areas of law.\r\n\r\nWe encourage our clients to come into our office for consultations or meetings. That way we can always sit down and try to address what’s going on in the client’s life.', 'About The Firm Video Transcript', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-the-firm-video-transcript', '', '', '2013-10-23 12:07:32', '2013-10-23 12:07:32', '', '0', 'http://brentbowen.com/?page_id=385', '0', 'page', '', '0');
