 for a Pilot Point DWI case involving an assistant coach.\r\n\r\n<dl><dt><strong>Areas of Practice: </strong></dt><dd>Criminal Law</dd><dd>DUI/DWI</dd><dd>White Collar Crimes</dd><dd>Family Law</dd><dd>Adoption</dd><dd>Child Support</dd><dd>Custody &amp; Visitation</dd><dd>Divorce</dd></dl><dl><dt><strong>Bar Admissions:</strong></dt><dd>Texas, 2002</dd><dd>Kansas, 2003</dd><dd>U.S. District Court District of Kansas, 2003</dd></dl><dl><dt><strong>Education:</strong></dt><dd>Washburn University School of Law, Topeka, Kansas, 2002\r\nJ.D.\r\n<em>Honors: </em>Moot Court, 2001 – 2002</dd></dl><dl><dd>Baylor University, Waco, Texas, 1999\r\nB.A.\r\nMajor:  Political Science</dd></dl><dl><dd>Samford University, Birmingham, Alabama</dd></dl><dl><dt><strong>Professional Associations and Memberships:</strong></dt><dd>Texas Bar Association</dd><dd></dd></dl><dl><dd>Kansas Bar Association</dd><dd></dd></dl><dl><dd>Denton County Bar Association</dd><dd></dd></dl><dl><dd>Texas District and County Attorney Association</dd><dd></dd></dl><dl><dd>Texas Criminal Defense Lawyers Association</dd><dd></dd></dl><dl><dd>Denton Criminal Defense Lawyer’s Association, 2006</dd><dd>Treasurer</dd></dl><dl><dd>Denton Criminal Defense Lawyer’s Association, 2007 – Present</dd><dd>President</dd></dl><dl><dt><strong>Past Employment Positions:</strong></dt><dd>Shawnee County District Attorney’s Office</dd></dl><dl><dd>Johnson County District Attorney’s Office, Assistant County Attorney</dd></dl><dl><dd>Denton County District Attorney’s Office, Assistant District Attorney, 2003 – 2004</dd></dl><dl><dd>Jackson &amp; Hagen, 2004 – 2006</dd></dl><dl><dt><strong>Fraternities/Sororities:</strong></dt><dd>Sigma Nu</dd></dl>', 'Brent Bowen', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '275-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-25 12:57:55', '2013-10-25 12:57:55', '', '275', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/275-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('396', '1', '2013-10-25 12:58:08', '2013-10-25 12:58:08', '<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-282\" alt=\"chrysandra-bowen\" src=\"http://brentbowen.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/chrysandra-bowen.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"280\" />Denton, Texas,\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><em>phone:\r\n</em></td>\r\n<td>  [number type=\"1\"]</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><em>fax:\r\n</em></td>\r\n<td>  (940) 566-0303</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\"><em>email:\r\n</em></td>\r\n<td><a href=\"http://www.brentbowen.com/contact-us/\">Email Me</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nChrysandra S. Bowen graduated Magna Cum Laude with honors with a B.A.S. in Addiction Counseling, with an emphasis in victim/witness services, and an A.A. with honors in Legal Assisting from Washburn University in Topeka, Kansas in December 2002. She received her Juris Doctorate from Texas Wesleyan School of Law in Fort Worth in December 2007.\r\n\r\nSince joining Bowen Law Group, Chrysandra has continued to develop a reputation as an aggressive advocate on behalf of her clients. Chrysandra is passionate about the welfare of her clients and has long had an affinity for children and family issues.\r\n\r\n“I fight for my clients! Decisions that clients make now can have an immense impact on their future. I make it my priority that my clients understand the entire process and all options that are available.”\r\n\r\nAt Bowen Law Group, Chrysandra handles a wide-variety of cases emphasizing in the areas of family law, adoption law, business organizations and estate planning. Chrysandra is known for her problem solving ability and hard-working nature. Chrysandra believes that in dealing with family law, it is necessary to think outside the box in order to create an arrangement that will work long-term.\r\nThe Kansas native spends her free time with her children and also loves to travel.\r\n\r\n<dl><dt><strong>Areas of Practice: </strong></dt><dd>Family Law</dd><dd>Adoption</dd><dd>Business Organization</dd><dd>Estate Planning</dd></dl><dl><dt><strong>Bar Admissions:</strong></dt><dd>Texas, 2008</dd></dl><dl><dt><strong>Education:</strong></dt><dd>Texas Wesleyan University School of Law, Fort Worth, Texas, December, 2007\r\nJuris Doctor</dd></dl><dl><dd>Washburn University, Topeka, Kansas, 2002\r\nBachlor of Applied Science\r\n<em>Honors: </em>Magna Cum Laude\r\nMajor:  Drug and Alcohol Counseling</dd></dl><dl><dd>Washburn University, Topeka, Kansas, 2001\r\n<em>Honors: </em>Associate, American Bar Association\r\nMajor:  Legal Assistant</dd></dl><dl><dt><strong>Professional Associations and Memberships:</strong></dt><dd>Denton County Bar Association, 2008 – Present</dd><dd>member</dd></dl><dl><dd>State Bar of Texas- Family Law Section, 2009 – Present</dd><dd>member</dd></dl><dl><dd>The College of the State Bar of Texas, 2009 – Present</dd><dd>member</dd></dl><dl><dt><strong>Fraternities/Sororities:</strong></dt><dd>Delta Gamma</dd></dl>', 'Chrysandra Bowen', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '281-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-25 12:58:08', '2013-10-25 12:58:08', '', '281', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/281-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
