on Expenses</em>.\r\n\r\nAt the Website, of the Internal Revenue Service, you will find information about tax rules and changes to those rules. You can link to this site for information about the IRS Adoption Taxpayer Identification Number, and forPublication 968, on the Adoption Tax Credit and Tax Exclusion. (http://www.irs.ustreas.gov/)\r\n<h4>State Tax Credits**</h4>\r\nSeveral states have enacted state tax credits for families adopting children from the public child welfare system in that state.\r\n<h4>Adoption from the Foster Care System</h4>\r\nIf you are interested in adopting a child who is currently waiting in foster care, often not only are fees kept to a bare minimum or even waived, but many of the children will be eligible for federally-funded or state-funded adoption subsidy payments which help you meet the child’s ongoing needs. Some children qualify for Social Security Insurance payments or Medicaid coverage because of their medical conditions.\r\n<h4>Reimbursement for Non-Recurring Adoption Expense</h4>\r\nAfter families have finalized the adoption of a child with special needs from the public child welfare system, they may be able to apply for reimbursement of expenses they paid related to the adoption, which may include home study fees, travel expenses to meet the child, and attorney fees.\r\n<h4>Possible Employer Benefits</h4>\r\nMany employers provide a range of benefits for families who adopt including paid or unpaid leave when a child arrives in the home, reimbursement of some portion of adoption expenses, assistance with adoption information and referral services. Contact your human resource department for information about benefits available, if any.\r\n\r\n<em>**Contact a Certified Public Accountant for more tax information.</em>', 'Adoption', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '349-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:24:59', '2013-10-26 09:24:59', '', '349', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/349-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('419', '1', '2013-10-26 09:26:42', '2013-10-26 09:26:42', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Texas Lawyer for Child Custody Issues</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/yZJozOowRbU?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"600\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nFor many people, child custody issues can be the most intense and emotional aspect of family law in Texas. They can also be the most confusing ones to navigate. Although parents and caretakers often have good intentions, it can be hard for them to determine what kind of custody arrangements are best for their children. That is what makes it is so necessary for individuals and families to obtain advice from an experienced divorce attorney in Texas.\r\n<h3>Setting Up a Child Custody Plan</h3>\r\nTexas divorce law states that parents must create a parenting plan that outlines each parent’s rights and responsibilities toward their children. At Bowen Law Group in Denton, Texas, we help families navigate the complexities of the legal system and establish a custody and visitation plan that works for everyone involved. Our family law attorneys will work to help your family resolve its child custody issues as smoothly and efficiently as possible. Protecting the interests of our clients and their children is our primary goal. Contact us today in order to discuss your situation and learn how we can help.\r\n<h3>Making Child Custody Modifications</h3>\r\nSometimes, long after a divorce has been finalized and custody arrangements have been put in place, the needs of the family change and an existing court order must be modified. It can be necessary for a positive reason (such as a parent obtaining a new job), a negative one (such as an abusive parent) or something as simple as the changing schedule of an older child. The lawyers at Bowen Law Group provide assistance to families in Denton who need their custody agreements modified, including helping clients understand how child relocation laws impact any existing custody and visitation orders.\r\n<h3>Handling Adoptions</h3>\r\nDuring some divorce proceedings, it becomes clear that the children involved need to be placed with either stepparents or foster parents. In these situations, our law firm facilitates stepparent and foster parent adoptions by working with Child and Family Services (CFS) or Child Protective Services (CPS).  Attorney Chrysandra S. Bowen is responsible for bringing together all the necessary parties for adoption proceedings in Denton. Her extensive background in counseling and dedication to her clients makes her a superior advocate for families during these personal—and often delicate—legal proceedings.\r\n<h3>Contact Us</h3>\r\nIf you would like to speak with a lawyer about child custody or adoption, please contact our law office in Denton, Texas, at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, 7 days a week to ensure that you get answers to your most pressing legal questions right when you need them. Call us today!', 'Child Custody', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '350-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:26:42', '2013-10-26 09:26:42', '', '350', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/350-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('420', '1', '2013-10-26 09:26:53', '2013-10-26 09:26:53', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Understanding and Effective Texas Divorce Lawyer</h2>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/XJb5rkxr5b4?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"600\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>The end of a marriage can be a very difficult thing to face. Even under the most amicable circumstances, divorce is a stressful and draining process for everyone involved, and the longer divorce proceedings last, the higher the emotional, mental and financial cost for a family.</p>\r\n<p>That’s why the attorneys at Bowen Law Group in Denton, Texas, work hard to resolve divorce cases as quickly and amicably as possible. The right lawyer can make a huge difference in how your divorce plays out, and our goal is to help you achieve maximum results with minimal stress for you and your loved ones.</p>\r\n<h3>What Happens during a Texas Divorce</h3>\r\n<p>Each divorce is unique. However, divorce proceedings in Texas usually start when one spouse files a petition for divorce, which requests that the court terminate the marriage based on either fault-based or no-fault-based grounds. The other spouse must then file an answer to the petition within a set period of time.</p>\r\n<p>Dissolution of marriage in Texas can involve a number of issues, including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Child custody and visitation</li>\r\n<li>Determination of child support</li>\r\n<li>Determination of alimony (spousal support)</li>\r\n<li>Division of property and debt</li>\r\n<li>Domestic violence and restraining orders</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>In many cases, divorce attorneys in Texas help the two parties attempt to reach a settlement, often using dispute resolution methods such as mediation or arbitration. If they are successful, the agreement is submitted to a judge, who approves it and grants the divorce. However, in the event a settlement cannot be reached, or the judge does not give approval, your divorce may proceed to trial. In either situation, it is critical for you to partner with a qualified divorce lawyer who can look out for your best interests.</p>\r\n<h3>Meet Chrysandra S. Bowen</h3>\r\n<p>Chrysandra S. Bowen is an organized, efficient divorce lawyer who manages all divorce cases at our law firm in Denton, Texas. Her background in therapy and counseling enables her to help resolve family conflicts and generate creative solutions that fit her clients’ needs. She recognizes that you are more than the details of your case, and will treat you with consideration and respect every step of the way.</p>\r\n<h3>Contact Us</h3>\r\n<p>If you live in Denton area and are facing a divorce, contact  our law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, so you can receive quick responses to your most pressing legal concerns. Our attorneys handle dissolution of marriage cases for clients throughout North Texas, including Lewisville, Denton, Flower Mound and other surrounding areas.  Contact us today!</p>\r\n', 'Divorce', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '348-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:26:53', '2013-10-26 09:26:53', '', '348', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/348-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('421', '1', '2013-10-26 09:27:23', '2013-10-26 09:27:23', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Criminal Defense After a Texas Drug Arrest</h2>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/B6ImImUX-bw?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>When you have been arrested for a drug crime in Texas, your future and your freedom could be at stake. Working with a criminal defense lawyer you feel comfortable with — someone who truly understands the issues involved — can help you achieve positive results.</p>\r\n<p>Attorney Brent Bowen is a former Denton County assistant district attorney who now handles criminal defense cases. He provides understanding and effective legal representation for people accused of crimes involving a wide range of drugs including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Marijuana</li>\r\n<li>Crack / cocaine</li>\r\n<li>Methamphetamine</li>\r\n<li>Heroin</li>\r\n<li>Cheese</li>\r\n<li>Prescription narcotics / pain killers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Under his guidance, our firm effectively handles drug possession arrest cases and other drug crimes including drug trafficking, growing and distributing illegal substances, and selling drugs. If you have been arrested for any of these crimes, contact us today to speak with a drug crime defense attorney.</p>\r\n<p>Each drug arrest involves unique facts and laws. The Bowen Law Group stays up to date on the most recent changes in the law, so we can use our in-depth knowledge to your advantage. Whether your drug arrest involved a violation of search and seizure laws, drug and gun charges for carrying a concealed weapon, or issues of juvenile law, we can help.</p>\r\n<h3>Talking About Addiction</h3>\r\n<p>The Bowen Law Group focuses on understanding clients, not just their cases. This means that we often look beyond the immediate legal issue, like a drug possession arrest, to the things that are really affecting you. Sometimes, this means talking to you about addiction.</p>\r\n<p>Frequently, a first drug possession arrest — or a second one — means hitting bottom. It can be a difficult time. Clients can benefit by addressing issues of drug abuse and addiction. We help refer clients to treatment programs. We recommend chemical dependency evaluations and counseling.</p>\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group for a Free Initial Consultation</h3>\r\n<p>To talk about your drug possession arrest with an attorney at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas law office at [number type=\"1\"]. We answer our phones 24 hours a day, 7 days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when an arrest has put your freedom at stake.</p>\r\n', 'Drug Crimes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '329-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:27:23', '2013-10-26 09:27:23', '', '329', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/329-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('422', '1', '2013-10-26 09:27:35', '2013-10-26 09:27:35', '<p><iframe width=\"600\" height=\"338\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/gKQIt-8YFyA?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe><br />\r\nIn Texas, there is a distinct difference between the offenses of DWI and DUI. DWI is the abbreviation for Driving While Intoxicated, while DUI is short for Driving Under the Influence. Consider the following:</p>\r\n<h2>DUI</h2>\r\n<p>Driving Under the Influence (DUI) is reserved for minors, <strong>people under 21 years of age</strong>. Under the influence is defined as any detectable amount of alcohol. Texas law has zero tolerance for minors with any detectable amount of alcohol. DUI is a class “C” misdemeanor. The maximum punishment for a Class “C” misdemeanor is a $500 fine. DUI also carries with it a driver’s license suspension when you’re arrested or when you receive the citation (ticket); there is also a separate and additional driver’s license suspension if you’re convicted. You can challenge a driver’s license suspension upon arrest through an ALR (Administrative License Review) hearing. The hearing must be requested within 15 days of arrest or citation. A police officer may request a breath test or simply issue a citation because the officer smells alcohol on the minor. A minor may refuse a breath test if arrested for DUI.</p>\r\n<h2>DWI</h2>\r\n<p>Driving While Intoxicated can apply to both minors and adults. An individual can be arrested for DWI whether they have consumed alcohol or drugs, even if the drugs are prescription drugs. Whether you take a breath test or not, you can be charged with DWI. DWI can be proven in one of three ways: (1) having a Blood Alcohol Content (BAC) of 0.08 or more, (2) not having your normal mental faculties, <strong>or</strong> (3) not having your normal physical faculties; due to alcohol or drugs. In Texas, DWI laws get tougher and tougher every year so it is important to consult with an attorney.</p>\r\n<h3>Breath or Blood Tests</h3>\r\n<p>Once you are arrested, an officer will request a blood or breath test. REMEMBER, YOU ARE ALREADY UNDER ARREST! Passing the breath test will not let you go home. It is important to be very careful in deciding to take a breath or blood test. If an officer asked you to blow into a little hand held gadget on the side of the road, it is okay; that reading is not admissible in court, except to show the mere presence of alcohol. If you admitted to drinking, the fact that you blew into that Portable Breath Test (PBT) has no relevance in a DWI trial. The most common question is, “CAN I REFUSE A BREATH OR BLOOD TEST?” The simple answer is “YES,” but there may be some consequences. It is important to know that YOU DO NOT HAVE A RIGHT TO AN ATTORNEY IN DECIDING TO TAKE A BREATH OR BLOOD TEST.</p>\r\n<h3>Consequences of Refusing a Breath or Blood Test:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If you refuse a breath test, DPS will try and suspend your driver’s license for a period of 180 days if you have never had a DWI before. If you have had a prior DWI or were asked to take a breath test before, the suspension could be two (2) years.</li>\r\n<li>The fact that you refused a breath test can be used against you in trial. Again, the courts have determined that you have no 5th Amendment protection against self incrimination regarding a Breath or Blood Test.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>IT IS IMPORTANT TO KNOW THAT YOU ONLY HAVE 15 DAYS TO REQUEST A HEARING TO CHALLENGE YOUR DRIVER’S LICENSE SUSPENSION.</strong></p>\r\n<h3>Consequences of Taking the Breath of Blood Test:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If you take a breath or blood test and the test reveals that you have an alcohol concentration of 0.08 or more, your driver’s license will be suspended for 90 days if this is your first DWI, or up to one (1) year if you have a prior DWI or alcohol suspension.</li>\r\n<li>You just gave the State evidence to convict you.</li>\r\n<li>Even if you pass the Breath or Blood test, you can still be charged and convicted of DWI.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', 'DUI vs DWI in Texas', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '322-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:27:35', '2013-10-26 09:27:35', '', '322', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/322-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
