INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('424', '1', '2013-10-26 09:37:15', '2013-10-26 09:37:15', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Legal Representation After an Arrest for a Theft Crime</h2>\r\n<p>Whether it resulted from an error in judgment, a false accusation or another situation entirely, an arrest for a theft crime should be taken seriously. And the first step to a serious criminal defense is to work with a knowledgeable and experienced attorney.</p>\r\n<p>Our criminal defense lawyer — Brent Bowen — is a former Denton County assistant district attorney who knows the law and who focuses on providing strong and effective criminal defense.</p>\r\n<p>Our Denton, Texas, law firm handles a broad range of felony and misdemeanor theft crimes in Texas state courts. Regardless of the allegations you face, we can talk openly with you about building a strong criminal defense:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Robbery and aggravated robbery</li>\r\n<li>Burglary</li>\r\n<li>Shoplifting</li>\r\n<li>Embezzlement / employee theft</li>\r\n<li>Auto theft</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Search and Seizure Issues</h3>\r\n<p>Each arrest is unique, but most arrests for theft crimes involve some issues related to search and seizure. WhenBowen Law Group handles your case, we always check to make sure that police followed the letter of the law.</p>\r\n<p>The law on search and seizure is constantly changing as existing laws are applied in new situations. The attorneys at Bowen Law Group stay current on the law so that we can offer quality representation to our clients.</p>\r\n<p>Our law firm philosophy is based on understanding our clients as people, not just as cases. Other issues, like financial hardship, drug or alcohol dependence, are often behind an arrest for a theft crime. As attorneys and counselors, we help you get the support you need for those issues — in addition to providing a strong and effective criminal defense in Texas courts.</p>\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\n<p>To talk about your criminal defense with an attorney at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when you need them most.</p>\r\n', 'Theft, Burglary, Robbery', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '330-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:37:15', '2013-10-26 09:37:15', '', '330', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/330-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('425', '1', '2013-10-26 09:37:29', '2013-10-26 09:37:29', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Sealing Your Texas Criminal Records</h2>\r\n<p><iframe width=\"600\" height=\"338\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/i43kB2sjjwk?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\r\n<p>Sometimes a criminal record can limit your future possibilities. It can keep you from getting the right job, or from moving in to the right apartment. But a knowledgeable attorney can help you take action under Texas law, sealing these records and protecting your future.</p>\r\n<p>At Bowen Law Group, located in Denton, Texas, we help clients with two different methods of criminal record expungement: expunction and nondisclosure. Depending on the circumstances surrounding your detention, arrest or conviction, either one might be the right fit for you.</p>\r\n<h3>What is the Difference Between Expunction and Non-Disclosure?</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Expunction:</strong> Expunction orders essentially erase all records of the offense — arrest records, court records and criminal history record information — from your criminal record. Expunction is only granted in certain circumstances, however. These include when a criminal case was dismissed or when you were found not guilty after a criminal trial. People who are not eligible for expunction may still be eligible for non-disclosure.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Non-disclosure:</strong> When a petition for non-disclosure is granted, criminal justice agencies are prohibited from giving information about the offense to the public. Usually, non-disclosure is granted in certain circumstances, like when you have successfully completed a deferred adjudication. For many offenses, there is a waiting period before you can file a petition for non-disclosure. Some offenses are eligible for non-disclosure immediately.</p>\r\n<p>Texas law also provides for the sealing of juvenile records. If your juvenile records are ordered sealed by the court, they are removed from the criminal history database. At Bowen Law Group, we can help with this and with other issues of juvenile law.</p>\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\n<p>To talk about expunction or non-disclosure with a lawyer at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when you need them most.</p>\r\n', 'Expunction and Non-Disclosure', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '337-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:37:29', '2013-10-26 09:37:29', '', '337', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/337-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('426', '1', '2013-10-26 09:39:34', '2013-10-26 09:39:34', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">When You Have Been Accused of a Probation Violation</h2>\r\n<p>There are many reasons why people are accused of violating probation — a DWI, a failed drug test or UA, failing to pay court-ordered fines or another offense. Often, a lapse in judgment or a false accusation is the reason.</p>\r\n<p>Regardless of the circumstances involved in your situation, Bowen Law Group can help. As a former Denton County assistant district attorney, Brent Bowen has in-depth knowledge of Texas law on probation violations. He provides strong and effective defenses for people accused of probation violations.</p>\r\n<p>Our Denton, Texas, law firm handles motions to revoke probation in Texas courts. We also provide representation in defense of motions to adjudicate, for men and women on adjudicated probation — those placed on formal probation without a conviction.</p>\r\n<h3>Understanding Our Clients — Not Just Their Cases</h3>\r\n<p>At Bowen Law Group, our law firm philosophy is based on understanding clients, not just their cases. This means that we often look beyond the immediate legal issue, like a probation violation, to the things that are really affecting you.</p>\r\n<p>Sometimes this means helping you get the resources you need to manage a drug, alcohol or anger management issue. Regardless of the issues that you face, you can trust Bowen Law Group for non-judgmental and confidential legal representation that gets real results.</p>\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\n<p>To talk about a probation violation or another criminal defense issue with a lawyer at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when you need them most.</p>\r\n', 'Probation Violations', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '338-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:39:34', '2013-10-26 09:39:34', '', '338', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/338-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('427', '1', '2013-10-26 09:41:40', '2013-10-26 09:41:40', '<p><iframe width=\"600\" height=\"338\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/Kf5v-qfiWgg?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>I was just arrested for DWI; should I wait to hire an attorney?</strong>NO. You have only 15 days from your arrest to request a hearing on your driver’s license. This hearing is very important to your case. You should act fast.</li>\r\n<li><strong>I was arrested; is this something I can really fight even if I don’t look good?</strong>YES. An experienced DWI attorney can defend a DWI case even if you look bad on tape or you failed the Breath test. There are several legal requirements that officers must follow on a DWI arrest.</li>\r\n<li><strong>The officer told me he had me on tape; will that work against me?</strong>NO. A video tape can often aid in your defense. You may look better than you thought, and the officer may have not done what he is trained to do. An experienced DWI attorney can make the tape work for you.</li>\r\n<li><strong>I took the breath test, and I think I failed; is the case over for me?</strong>ABSOLUTELY NOT. There are several things an officer must do in giving you a Breath or Blood test. Also, juries can return a not guilty verdict even with a Breath or Blood test.</li>\r\n<li><strong>I was told never to take a breath test. I was arrested; how do they show I was drunk?</strong>In Texas; intoxication can be proven one of three ways: (1) 0.08 or more, (2) not having your normal mental faculties, OR (3) not having your normal physical faculties.</li>\r\n<li><strong>If I take the Breath test or Blood test and pass, will the Police release me to go home and not file the DWI?</strong>NO. There are three ways the Government can prove intoxication. Police do not let you go home. When you are requested to take a Breath or Blood test, you are ALREADY UNDER ARREST. The Breath or Blood test is only a formality. The Police will not un-arrest you if you pass the breath test. A Blood test takes time get back from the lab.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Can I refuse the Breath or Blood test? Can the fact that I refused be used against me?</strong>Yes. The fact that you refused the Breath or Blood test can be used against you in your DWI trial; however, most people have been advised by friends, family, and others not to take the test. Unless you are POSITIVE you will pass, you probably should not take the Breath or Blood test.</li>\r\n<li><strong>I was involved in an accident and the officer requested that I take a Blood test; can they to that?</strong>Yes. In Texas, the officer has the option to request a Breath or a Blood test.</li>\r\n<li><strong>I decided to take a Blood test; can the case be defended?</strong>Yes. Blood tests are tough because juries tend to rely heavily on a Blood test. However, a skilled DWI lawyer who knows the procedures on how blood is tested and how blood is handled by police and the labs can give you the best defense possible. Just because you took the test does not mean the Government can present it to a jury in your DWI trial.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Can I be charged with DWI when all I did was take the medication the doctor prescribed?</strong>YES. The law allows you to be charged with DWI when you have legally taken drugs. You need a skilled DWI lawyer to address these issues.</li>\r\n<li><strong>The officer had me do some tests; what are they for?</strong>These were Field Sobriety Tests (FSTs). There are three standardized field sobriety tests – the HGN (eye test), the Walk and Turn, and the One Leg stand. Police use them when investigating a DWI to try and determine whether someone is intoxicated.</li>\r\n<li><strong>What does “standardized” mean, and how does that affect me?</strong>Standardized means that tests must be demonstrated, instructed, and performed the same way every time. It is important to have a skilled DWI attorney who knows what to look for to make sure the police officer demonstrated, instructed, and performed the tests with the adopted procedure.</li>\r\n<li><strong>What is an ALR, and can it be won?</strong>An ALR hearing is an Administrative License Review hearing. This is the hearing that determines whether or not your driver’s license will be suspended as a result of refusing or failing the breath or blood test when you where arrested for DWI or DUI. Yes, an ALR can be won. These hearings offer a wealth of information and are very important to your case.</li>\r\n<li><strong>I have to drive for work and there is no public transportation; how do I get there?</strong>If an ALR hearing is requested within the first 15 days, your driving privileges are restored until the ALR judge makes a determination to suspend your driver’s license. If the judge suspends your driver’s license, you may be eligible for an occupational driver’s license.</li>\r\n<li><strong>If I win my DWI trial, can I get the records destroyed?</strong>YES. In most cases, if you are acquitted of DWI or DUI, you are entitled to have those records expunged (destroyed), and often the ALR suspension can also be removed from your driving record.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', 'DWI FAQs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '323-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:41:40', '2013-10-26 09:41:40', '', '323', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/323-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('428', '1', '2013-10-26 09:42:01', '2013-10-26 09:42:01', '<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/EqbqPwNGxPU?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><strong>When arrested for DWI you only have 15 days to request a hearing to save your drivers license</strong></p>\r\n<h2>Did you know…</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Driving under the influence (DUI) and driving while intoxicated (DWI) are <strong>two separate charges</strong> in Texas?</li>\r\n<li>If you have been charged with drunk driving, you can face both criminal <strong>and</strong> civil penalties?</li>\r\n<li>You only have <strong>15 days</strong> after you have been arrested to request a hearing if you want to save your driver’s license?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>These are only a few of the details you must consider if you are charged with DWI in North Texas, and they are ones you can’t afford to deal with alone. You need help from an experienced DWI attorney in Texas you can trust – one who is deeply committed to protecting your rights.</p>\r\n<p>Fortunately, the Texas DWI attorneys at Bowen Law Group are here to help. Our law firm provides a number of criminal defense services to adults and juveniles, including private drivers with occupational driver’s licenses (ODL). We pride ourselves on being some of the most focused and accomplished attorneys in Denton, Texas.</p>\r\n<h3>A Comprehensive DWI Defense</h3>\r\n<p>For people who have been charged with drunk driving, the idea of facing criminal and civil penalties can be overwhelming. Many individuals who contact our office in Denton worry about the loss of their driver’s license, or other repercussions. The lawyers at Bowen Law Group have the knowledge and experience to handle all aspects of your Denton DWI defense, including the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Administrative license hearings</li>\r\n<li>Driver’s License Appeals</li>\r\n<li>Criminal hearings</li>\r\n<li>Plea agreements, trials and appeals</li>\r\n<li>Drug charge defense</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>A Prosecutor’s Advantage</h3>\r\n<p>As a former prosecutor, Brent D. Bowen has worked on hundreds of DWI cases, and therefore knows how to anticipate and respond to the state’s case effectively. Not only that, but our criminal attorneys in Denton work hard to stay well-informed about changes that occur in Texas DWI laws. Although most DWI cases are resolved by agreement, our lawyers also have the litigation experience to fight for your rights and interests if your case goes to trial. Our goal is simple: to protect your freedoms and be the best advocates we can be for you.</p>\r\n<p>If you’d like to learn more about our DWI defense or other criminal defense services, contact us to schedule a free consultation with an attorney at our office in Denton. We would be happy to evaluate your case for you. We serve individuals who live throughout North Texas, including the counties of Denton, Collin, Tarrant, Wise and Cooke.</p>\r\n<p>You’re not alone. You have options. Call the Bowen Law Group to find out what they are.</p>\r\n', ' DWI Defense', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '312-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:42:01', '2013-10-26 09:42:01', '', '312', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/312-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('429', '1', '2013-10-26 09:46:23', '2013-10-26 09:46:23', '<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/yv8Wmw0alIQ?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"601\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>The lawyers at Bowen Law Group are committed to helping families seek efficient and productive solutions to difficult family disputes. If you need to speak with a lawyer about a divorce or family law matter in the counties of Denton, Dallas, Tarrant, Wise or Cooke, we are pleased to be of assistance.</p>\r\n<p>We take an aggressive yet reasoned approach to divorce and family disputes that has enabled many of our clients to achieve legal and personal closure in a relatively short period of time. We always put the interests of our clients first, and we will not fight or cause undue delay for the sake of pride or profit.</p>\r\n<p>Contact us for assistance with any of the following family law matters:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Divorce</li>\r\n<li>Property division</li>\r\n<li>Child custody and visitation</li>\r\n<li>Adoption</li>\r\n<li>Defense of parents in Child Protective Services (CPS) investigations</li>\r\n<li>Family law Mediation</li>\r\n<li>Suit affecting parent-child relationship (SAPCR)</li>\r\n<li>Protective and Restraining Orders</li>\r\n<li>Modifications</li>\r\n<li>Domestic Violence</li>\r\n<li>Ad litem services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Protecting Your Rights in Family Law Cases</h3>\r\n<p>Our goal in each case is to help people protect their financial and parental rights. Our attorneys are skilled negotiators and family court trial lawyers who have achieved positive results for clients in family law disputes involving complex division of property issues. When forming divorce settlements, we vigorously fight for the rights of the parents while keeping the best interests of the children in mind.</p>\r\n<h3>Schedule an Appointment With a North Texas Attorney</h3>\r\n<p>It is important to speak with a lawyer and fully understand your rights and responsibilities if you are involved in a legal dispute involving a spouse or children. We offer a very informative consultation. We give clients a candid assessment of their case so they may proceed in an informed manner.</p>\r\n<p>To learn more about your rights and options, call our Denton office at [number type=\"1\"]. You may also contact us by e-mail.</p>\r\n', 'Family Law', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '291-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:46:23', '2013-10-26 09:46:23', '', '291', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/291-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('430', '1', '2013-10-26 09:47:49', '2013-10-26 09:47:49', '<h3>Child Custody Modifications</h3>\r\n<p><iframe width=\"600\" height=\"338\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/McbuiXEV0I0?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\r\n<p>Nothing is more important to parents than their child. If you are involved in a child custody or visitation dispute in Denton, Tarrant or Wise County, Texas, we encourage you to schedule a consultation at Bowen Law Group</p>\r\n<p>If you have been divorced and a parenting plan no longer serves the best interest of your children, you need experienced legal representation to handle your case. At Bowen Law Group, we offer experienced and dedicated legal services to people throughout Denton, Tarrant and Wise County. We take time to listen to clients, answer their questions and provide candid advice regarding their case. We are passionately defensive of clients’ parental rights and always pursue the best possible result in each case.</p>\r\n<h3>Child Support Modifications</h3>\r\n<p>Do you feel you are paying too much child support? Do you think you should be receiving more child support?</p>\r\n<p>If you live in Denton or Wise County, Bowen Law Group can help. From our law offices in Denton, we represent clients in a wide range of family law matters, including child support modification proceedings.</p>\r\n<p>If you choose to retain our firm for your case, we can perform a detailed child support calculation on your behalf, taking into account your income and the child support guidelines. In addition to handling child support modification proceedings for ex-spouses who have divorced, we represent unwed mothers and fathers who have been involved in paternity proceedings and are seeking to modify a previous child support order.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Contact an Attorney</strong></p>\r\n<p>To speak with an attorney or schedule an appointment about a child custody or child support modification petition, contact Bowen Law Group.</p>\r\n', 'Modifications', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '362-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:47:49', '2013-10-26 09:47:49', '', '362', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/362-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('431', '1', '2013-10-26 09:48:00', '2013-10-26 09:48:00', '<p>Your Divorce Decree may contain strict orders about a parent relocating a child. That is why it makes sense to discuss your situation with an experienced lawyer before you move your child. If you are the parent with whom the child resides the majority of the time and wish to relocate, don’t take any chances. Do your homework before taking action.</p>\r\n<p>If you are the parent who does not want your child to relocate, you must follow the statutory requirements by filing your objection within the required time period. Whether you are the relocating primary parent or the parent objecting to proposed relocation, seeking the advice of an attorney experienced in relocation is extremely important.</p>\r\n<p>To learn more about relocating, <a href=\"http://www.brentbowen.com/contact-us/\">contact our Denton County Law Firm</a>.</p>\r\n', 'Relocating With A Child', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '361-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:48:00', '2013-10-26 09:48:00', '', '361', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/361-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('432', '1', '2013-10-26 09:48:12', '2013-10-26 09:48:12', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Restraining and Protective Orders in Divorce and Family Law Cases</h2>\r\n<p>Many people assume that restraining orders are only obtained during divorce cases in Texas as a result of extreme violence. While domestic violence is certainly a valid reason, restraining orders can be obtained for multiple other reasons during a divorce case in Denton as well, including the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To prevent a spouse from entering the marital home.</li>\r\n<li>To prevent a spouse from entering a vehicle of the marriage.</li>\r\n<li>As a result of one spouse changing insurance policy coverage.</li>\r\n<li>The result of a spouse’s unwise spending habits, such as recklessly giving away property.</li>\r\n<li>A child has been threatened or otherwise harmed by a parent</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Naturally, a protective order is not something to be used lightly or for vindictive reasons. However, if you believe a protective order is necessary to protect you and your children, you should contact your local District Attorney’s office to obtain an application immediately. A protective order is especially critical to stop an abuser from committing violent acts, including threatening, harassing or stalking.</p>\r\n<p>The attorneys at Bowen Law Group provide legal assistance to individuals and families throughout North Texas, including Denton, Wise, Cooke and Tarrant counties. Our highly skilled and knowledgeable lawyers offer representation concerning a number of divorce and family law issues in Denton, including motions for a protective order or a restraining order. At the same time, we also represent clients who wish to oppose motions for such orders. If you live in Denton and are seeking to obtain or oppose a restraining order, don’t wait. Contact  <a href=\"http://www.brentbowen.com/contact-us/\">Chrysandra S. Bowen</a> today in order to get the help you need.</p>\r\n<h3>Things to Remember about Restraining Orders and Protective Orders</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A restraining order and a protective order are not the same thing. A restraining order prohibits someone from engaging in behavior that has been restrained by the court, while a protective order is a court order that makes one person stay away from another. Only a protective order is criminally enforceable, which means the police can immediately be called for assistance and the person in violation of the order can be arrested.</li>\r\n<li><strong>You do not need to be married</strong> to someone in order to get a protective order or restraining order against them. If you and the abuser are divorced, lived together, had a child together (even if you weren’t married), or had a dating relationship, you meet the requirements to obtain a protective or restraining order. You can also obtain one if you and the abuser are related by blood, or are foster parent and foster child.</li>\r\n<li><strong>You must go to court</strong> in order to get a protective order or a restraining order. At the same time, the person you want to serve the order against must have the opportunity to come to court on the hearing day and object to the order.</li>\r\n<li>You <strong>cannot</strong> get a protective order due to <strong>mental abuse alone</strong>. You must show that physical abuse (hitting, choking, kicking, slapping, etc.) has occurred in the past or is likely to occur in the future (due to a clear and imminent threat of violence). Mental abuse and emotional abuse are not part of the definition of family violence in the Texas Family Code.</li>\r\n<li>A protective order can be in effect for up to two years, and can be renewed if necessary.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you have questions or would like additional information about restraining orders, protective orders or other aspects of divorce law, contact our office in Denton today. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, allowing you to consistently get immediate assistance when you need it.</p>\r\n', 'Restraining Orders in Divorce Family Law Cases', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '360-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 09:48:12', '2013-10-26 09:48:12', '', '360', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/360-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
