INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('451', '1', '2013-10-26 11:33:46', '2013-10-26 11:33:46', '<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/esn8sg7TDWk?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nA criminal conviction, even a misdemeanor conviction, can have severe repercussions. If you have been charged with a crime, it is critical to obtain legal counsel to protect your rights.\r\n\r\nAt Bowen Law Group, we provide experienced and aggressive defense services on behalf of adults and juveniles charged with a crime. With offices in Denton and Lewisville, Texas, we are pleased to represent clients throughout the region, including people in Denton, Dallas, Tarrant, Wise, and Cooke counties.\r\n\r\nWe handle a wide range of felony and misdemeanor criminal law matters, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>DUI / DWI</li>\r\n	<li>Assault, including sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Injury to child/elderly</li>\r\n	<li>Drug possession and other drug crimes</li>\r\n	<li>Burglary and robbery</li>\r\n	<li>Probation violation</li>\r\n	<li>Expunction and nondisclosures</li>\r\n	<li>Juvenile law</li>\r\n	<li>Administrative license review hearing</li>\r\n	<li>Occupational driver’s license protection</li>\r\n	<li>Hearings, trial, sentencing, appeal</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Former Prosecutors Protecting Your Rights</h3>\r\nThe attorneys at our firm are former prosecutors. In fact, Attorney Brent D. Bowen was a prosecutor for Shawnee County, Johnson County and Denton County. This experience better enables us to see both sides of a case and thoroughly scrutinize evidence on behalf of the clients we represent.\r\n<h3>Legal Assistance Tailored to Your Needs</h3>\r\nWhen handling a criminal law case, our goal is to provide immediate and long-term assistance to the people we represent. In some cases, litigation works best to serve the needs of clients. In other cases, a plea agreement resulting in a reduced charge or reduction of criminal penalties may be best. We will pursue whichever option leads to the better result.\r\n\r\nIn each case we handle, we place a strong emphasis on providing lasting results for the client we represent. Many people who are arrested on criminal charges are facing difficult personal challenges that may involve chemical dependency, mental illness or anger management issues. In cases where clients may benefit from assistance and ask for our help, we are pleased to provide assistance with the location of appropriate medical and mental health professionals.\r\n<h3>Contact a Texas Criminal Defense Attorney</h3>\r\nTo schedule a free consultation to learn more about your rights and options, call our Denton office at [number type=\"1\"] or contact our criminal defense lawyers by e-mail.', 'Criminal Defense', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '290-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 11:33:46', '2013-10-26 11:33:46', '', '290', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/290-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('452', '1', '2013-10-26 11:35:24', '2013-10-26 11:35:24', '<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/gKQIt-8YFyA?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\nIn Texas, there is a distinct difference between the offenses of DWI and DUI. DWI is the abbreviation for Driving While Intoxicated, while DUI is short for Driving Under the Influence. Consider the following:\r\n<h2>DUI</h2>\r\nDriving Under the Influence (DUI) is reserved for minors, <strong>people under 21 years of age</strong>. Under the influence is defined as any detectable amount of alcohol. Texas law has zero tolerance for minors with any detectable amount of alcohol. DUI is a class “C” misdemeanor. The maximum punishment for a Class “C” misdemeanor is a $500 fine. DUI also carries with it a driver’s license suspension when you’re arrested or when you receive the citation (ticket); there is also a separate and additional driver’s license suspension if you’re convicted. You can challenge a driver’s license suspension upon arrest through an ALR (Administrative License Review) hearing. The hearing must be requested within 15 days of arrest or citation. A police officer may request a breath test or simply issue a citation because the officer smells alcohol on the minor. A minor may refuse a breath test if arrested for DUI.\r\n<h2>DWI</h2>\r\nDriving While Intoxicated can apply to both minors and adults. An individual can be arrested for DWI whether they have consumed alcohol or drugs, even if the drugs are prescription drugs. Whether you take a breath test or not, you can be charged with DWI. DWI can be proven in one of three ways: (1) having a Blood Alcohol Content (BAC) of 0.08 or more, (2) not having your normal mental faculties, <strong>or</strong> (3) not having your normal physical faculties; due to alcohol or drugs. In Texas, DWI laws get tougher and tougher every year so it is important to consult with an attorney.\r\n<h3>Breath or Blood Tests</h3>\r\nOnce you are arrested, an officer will request a blood or breath test. REMEMBER, YOU ARE ALREADY UNDER ARREST! Passing the breath test will not let you go home. It is important to be very careful in deciding to take a breath or blood test. If an officer asked you to blow into a little hand held gadget on the side of the road, it is okay; that reading is not admissible in court, except to show the mere presence of alcohol. If you admitted to drinking, the fact that you blew into that Portable Breath Test (PBT) has no relevance in a DWI trial. The most common question is, “CAN I REFUSE A BREATH OR BLOOD TEST?” The simple answer is “YES,” but there may be some consequences. It is important to know that YOU DO NOT HAVE A RIGHT TO AN ATTORNEY IN DECIDING TO TAKE A BREATH OR BLOOD TEST.\r\n<h3>Consequences of Refusing a Breath or Blood Test:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>If you refuse a breath test, DPS will try and suspend your driver’s license for a period of 180 days if you have never had a DWI before. If you have had a prior DWI or were asked to take a breath test before, the suspension could be two (2) years.</li>\r\n	<li>The fact that you refused a breath test can be used against you in trial. Again, the courts have determined that you have no 5th Amendment protection against self incrimination regarding a Breath or Blood Test.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>IT IS IMPORTANT TO KNOW THAT YOU ONLY HAVE 15 DAYS TO REQUEST A HEARING TO CHALLENGE YOUR DRIVER’S LICENSE SUSPENSION.</strong>\r\n<h3>Consequences of Taking the Breath of Blood Test:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>If you take a breath or blood test and the test reveals that you have an alcohol concentration of 0.08 or more, your driver’s license will be suspended for 90 days if this is your first DWI, or up to one (1) year if you have a prior DWI or alcohol suspension.</li>\r\n	<li>You just gave the State evidence to convict you.</li>\r\n	<li>Even if you pass the Breath or Blood test, you can still be charged and convicted of DWI.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'DUI vs DWI in Texas', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '322-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 11:35:24', '2013-10-26 11:35:24', '', '322', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/322-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('453', '1', '2013-10-26 11:36:10', '2013-10-26 11:36:10', '<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/Kf5v-qfiWgg?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>I was just arrested for DWI; should I wait to hire an attorney?</strong>NO. You have only 15 days from your arrest to request a hearing on your driver’s license. This hearing is very important to your case. You should act fast.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>I was arrested; is this something I can really fight even if I don’t look good?</strong>YES. An experienced DWI attorney can defend a DWI case even if you look bad on tape or you failed the Breath test. There are several legal requirements that officers must follow on a DWI arrest.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The officer told me he had me on tape; will that work against me?</strong>NO. A video tape can often aid in your defense. You may look better than you thought, and the officer may have not done what he is trained to do. An experienced DWI attorney can make the tape work for you.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>I took the breath test, and I think I failed; is the case over for me?</strong>ABSOLUTELY NOT. There are several things an officer must do in giving you a Breath or Blood test. Also, juries can return a not guilty verdict even with a Breath or Blood test.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>I was told never to take a breath test. I was arrested; how do they show I was drunk?</strong>In Texas; intoxication can be proven one of three ways: (1) 0.08 or more, (2) not having your normal mental faculties, OR (3) not having your normal physical faculties.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>If I take the Breath test or Blood test and pass, will the Police release me to go home and not file the DWI?</strong>NO. There are three ways the Government can prove intoxication. Police do not let you go home. When you are requested to take a Breath or Blood test, you are ALREADY UNDER ARREST. The Breath or Blood test is only a formality. The Police will not un-arrest you if you pass the breath test. A Blood test takes time get back from the lab.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Can I refuse the Breath or Blood test? Can the fact that I refused be used against me?</strong>Yes. The fact that you refused the Breath or Blood test can be used against you in your DWI trial; however, most people have been advised by friends, family, and others not to take the test. Unless you are POSITIVE you will pass, you probably should not take the Breath or Blood test.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>I was involved in an accident and the officer requested that I take a Blood test; can they to that?</strong>Yes. In Texas, the officer has the option to request a Breath or a Blood test.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>I decided to take a Blood test; can the case be defended?</strong>Yes. Blood tests are tough because juries tend to rely heavily on a Blood test. However, a skilled DWI lawyer who knows the procedures on how blood is tested and how blood is handled by police and the labs can give you the best defense possible. Just because you took the test does not mean the Government can present it to a jury in your DWI trial.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Can I be charged with DWI when all I did was take the medication the doctor prescribed?</strong>YES. The law allows you to be charged with DWI when you have legally taken drugs. You need a skilled DWI lawyer to address these issues.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The officer had me do some tests; what are they for?</strong>These were Field Sobriety Tests (FSTs). There are three standardized field sobriety tests – the HGN (eye test), the Walk and Turn, and the One Leg stand. Police use them when investigating a DWI to try and determine whether someone is intoxicated.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>What does “standardized” mean, and how does that affect me?</strong>Standardized means that tests must be demonstrated, instructed, and performed the same way every time. It is important to have a skilled DWI attorney who knows what to look for to make sure the police officer demonstrated, instructed, and performed the tests with the adopted procedure.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>What is an ALR, and can it be won?</strong>An ALR hearing is an Administrative License Review hearing. This is the hearing that determines whether or not your driver’s license will be suspended as a result of refusing or failing the breath or blood test when you where arrested for DWI or DUI. Yes, an ALR can be won. These hearings offer a wealth of information and are very important to your case.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>I have to drive for work and there is no public transportation; how do I get there?</strong>If an ALR hearing is requested within the first 15 days, your driving privileges are restored until the ALR judge makes a determination to suspend your driver’s license. If the judge suspends your driver’s license, you may be eligible for an occupational driver’s license.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>If I win my DWI trial, can I get the records destroyed?</strong>YES. In most cases, if you are acquitted of DWI or DUI, you are entitled to have those records expunged (destroyed), and often the ALR suspension can also be removed from your driving record.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'DWI FAQs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '323-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 11:36:10', '2013-10-26 11:36:10', '', '323', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/323-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('454', '1', '2013-10-26 11:39:51', '2013-10-26 11:39:51', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Criminal Defense for Assault Allegations</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/phikvDuso2A?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nWhen allegations of violence lead to an arrest, the situation is often difficult and emotional. At Bowen Law Group, in Denton, Texas, we offer confidential and non-judgmental criminal defense that helps you achieve positive results in Texas state courts.\r\n\r\nAt Bowen Law Group, criminal defense lawyer Brent Bowen is a former Denton County assistant district attorney who is respected by prosecutors. Brent has a reputation for straight talk and effective action in Texas state courts.\r\n<h3>Representing People Accused of Violent Crimes in Texas State Courts</h3>\r\nWe represent people accused of a wide range of violent crimes, including assault, sexual assault and other violent conduct. We also handle family law disputes, like assault allegations related to domestic violence or allegations of child abuse made by Child Protective Services (CPS). Attorney Chrysandra Bowen handles these family issues with the attention and sensitivity they deserve, using her counseling background.\r\n\r\nWhen we take your assault case, we begin exploring all your options. Sometimes self defense is an effective explanation for your actions. Other times, witnesses are not credible. Regardless of the situation, our aim is to achieve positive results. However, there are times when the clients would benefit from anger management or family counseling.\r\n\r\nTexas law has changed. Now homeowners have no duty to retreat before defending themselves against dangerous intruders in their own homes. However, because each situation is unique, it is best to talk about your situation with an experienced lawyer.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\nTo talk about the assault allegations you face with an attorney at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when you need them most.', 'Assault', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '331-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 11:39:51', '2013-10-26 11:39:51', '', '331', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/331-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('455', '1', '2013-10-26 11:39:58', '2013-10-26 11:39:58', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Criminal Defense After a Texas Drug Arrest</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/B6ImImUX-bw?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nWhen you have been arrested for a drug crime in Texas, your future and your freedom could be at stake. Working with a criminal defense lawyer you feel comfortable with — someone who truly understands the issues involved — can help you achieve positive results.\r\n\r\nAttorney Brent Bowen is a former Denton County assistant district attorney who now handles criminal defense cases. He provides understanding and effective legal representation for people accused of crimes involving a wide range of drugs including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Marijuana</li>\r\n	<li>Crack / cocaine</li>\r\n	<li>Methamphetamine</li>\r\n	<li>Heroin</li>\r\n	<li>Cheese</li>\r\n	<li>Prescription narcotics / pain killers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nUnder his guidance, our firm effectively handles drug possession arrest cases and other drug crimes including drug trafficking, growing and distributing illegal substances, and selling drugs. If you have been arrested for any of these crimes, contact us today to speak with a drug crime defense attorney.\r\n\r\nEach drug arrest involves unique facts and laws. The Bowen Law Group stays up to date on the most recent changes in the law, so we can use our in-depth knowledge to your advantage. Whether your drug arrest involved a violation of search and seizure laws, drug and gun charges for carrying a concealed weapon, or issues of juvenile law, we can help.\r\n<h3>Talking About Addiction</h3>\r\nThe Bowen Law Group focuses on understanding clients, not just their cases. This means that we often look beyond the immediate legal issue, like a drug possession arrest, to the things that are really affecting you. Sometimes, this means talking to you about addiction.\r\n\r\nFrequently, a first drug possession arrest — or a second one — means hitting bottom. It can be a difficult time. Clients can benefit by addressing issues of drug abuse and addiction. We help refer clients to treatment programs. We recommend chemical dependency evaluations and counseling.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group for a Free Initial Consultation</h3>\r\nTo talk about your drug possession arrest with an attorney at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas law office at [number type=\"1\"]. We answer our phones 24 hours a day, 7 days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when an arrest has put your freedom at stake.', 'Drug Crimes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '329-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 11:39:58', '2013-10-26 11:39:58', '', '329', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/329-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('456', '1', '2013-10-26 11:42:39', '2013-10-26 11:42:39', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Denton, Texas, Attorney for Juvenile Law Issues</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/ckivCodlNas?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nKids and teens are not adults, and — unless the allegations are especially serious — Texas law does not treat them that way. In Texas, juvenile cases are civil rather than criminal in nature.\r\n\r\nIn order to achieve results, it is important to work with a lawyer who knows Texas juvenile law. At Bowen Law Group, attorney Brent Bowen is a former Denton County assistant district attorney who is experienced in defending young people in juvenile matters.\r\n\r\nOur Denton, Texas, law firm handles a wide range of offenses under Texas juvenile law:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Minor in possession</li>\r\n	<li>Drug crimes</li>\r\n	<li>Assault</li>\r\n	<li>Sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Robbery</li>\r\n	<li>Shoplifting</li>\r\n	<li>Burglary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition to representing offenders in juvenile court, we also handle related administrative matters, like suspensions and expulsions from Texas schools. We also talk to our clients about sealing juvenile records, or expunction and non-disclosure of criminal records after an offense.\r\n<h3>Quick Action for Juvenile Detention Hearings</h3>\r\nInstead of being arrested, minors are “detained” or “taken into custody.” Under Texas law, if a juvenile is detained, he or she must be held in a special facility separate from adult violators. The law requires that a detention hearing be held before a judge — usually the day after the child was taken into custody. Only a judge after a detention hearing can release a juvenile to a parent, guardian or custodian.\r\n\r\nAt Bowen Law Group, we understand the stress and worry families feel when a child has been taken into custody. We have a 24-hour, seven-day-a-week phone line so that we can respond quickly to juvenile law issues — especially when your family needs it most.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\nTo talk with an attorney at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns.', ' Juvenile Law', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '336-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 11:42:39', '2013-10-26 11:42:39', '', '336', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/336-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('457', '1', '2013-10-26 11:43:21', '2013-10-26 11:43:21', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Sealing Your Texas Criminal Records</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/i43kB2sjjwk?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nSometimes a criminal record can limit your future possibilities. It can keep you from getting the right job, or from moving in to the right apartment. But a knowledgeable attorney can help you take action under Texas law, sealing these records and protecting your future.\r\n\r\nAt Bowen Law Group, located in Denton, Texas, we help clients with two different methods of criminal record expungement: expunction and nondisclosure. Depending on the circumstances surrounding your detention, arrest or conviction, either one might be the right fit for you.\r\n<h3>What is the Difference Between Expunction and Non-Disclosure?</h3>\r\n<strong>Expunction:</strong> Expunction orders essentially erase all records of the offense — arrest records, court records and criminal history record information — from your criminal record. Expunction is only granted in certain circumstances, however. These include when a criminal case was dismissed or when you were found not guilty after a criminal trial. People who are not eligible for expunction may still be eligible for non-disclosure.\r\n\r\n<strong>Non-disclosure:</strong> When a petition for non-disclosure is granted, criminal justice agencies are prohibited from giving information about the offense to the public. Usually, non-disclosure is granted in certain circumstances, like when you have successfully completed a deferred adjudication. For many offenses, there is a waiting period before you can file a petition for non-disclosure. Some offenses are eligible for non-disclosure immediately.\r\n\r\nTexas law also provides for the sealing of juvenile records. If your juvenile records are ordered sealed by the court, they are removed from the criminal history database. At Bowen Law Group, we can help with this and with other issues of juvenile law.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\nTo talk about expunction or non-disclosure with a lawyer at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when you need them most.', 'Expunction and Non-Disclosure', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '337-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 11:43:21', '2013-10-26 11:43:21', '', '337', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/337-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('458', '1', '2013-10-26 11:44:53', '2013-10-26 11:44:53', '<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/yv8Wmw0alIQ?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nThe lawyers at Bowen Law Group are committed to helping families seek efficient and productive solutions to difficult family disputes. If you need to speak with a lawyer about a divorce or family law matter in the counties of Denton, Dallas, Tarrant, Wise or Cooke, we are pleased to be of assistance.\r\n\r\nWe take an aggressive yet reasoned approach to divorce and family disputes that has enabled many of our clients to achieve legal and personal closure in a relatively short period of time. We always put the interests of our clients first, and we will not fight or cause undue delay for the sake of pride or profit.\r\n\r\nContact us for assistance with any of the following family law matters:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Divorce</li>\r\n	<li>Property division</li>\r\n	<li>Child custody and visitation</li>\r\n	<li>Adoption</li>\r\n	<li>Defense of parents in Child Protective Services (CPS) investigations</li>\r\n	<li>Family law Mediation</li>\r\n	<li>Suit affecting parent-child relationship (SAPCR)</li>\r\n	<li>Protective and Restraining Orders</li>\r\n	<li>Modifications</li>\r\n	<li>Domestic Violence</li>\r\n	<li>Ad litem services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Protecting Your Rights in Family Law Cases</h3>\r\nOur goal in each case is to help people protect their financial and parental rights. Our attorneys are skilled negotiators and family court trial lawyers who have achieved positive results for clients in family law disputes involving complex division of property issues. When forming divorce settlements, we vigorously fight for the rights of the parents while keeping the best interests of the children in mind.\r\n<h3>Schedule an Appointment With a North Texas Attorney</h3>\r\nIt is important to speak with a lawyer and fully understand your rights and responsibilities if you are involved in a legal dispute involving a spouse or children. We offer a very informative consultation. We give clients a candid assessment of their case so they may proceed in an informed manner.\r\n\r\nTo learn more about your rights and options, call our Denton office at [number type=\"1\"]. You may also contact us by e-mail.', 'Family Law', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '291-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 11:44:53', '2013-10-26 11:44:53', '', '291', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/291-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('459', '1', '2013-10-26 11:46:31', '2013-10-26 11:46:31', '<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/JZQY-1JY4Qg?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nAdoption is a joyous opportunity for all parties; a child is placed with a family who needs them. However, while an adoption can be a joyous event, there are many legal issues that can stop the proceeding in its tracks. Working with an experienced adoption attorney is important in any type of adoption. The laws governing the adoption process are complex, whether they are a step-parent, foster parent or un-related adoptive parent adoptions. To avoid delay and disappointment in your adoption, contact an experienced adoption attorney at Bowen Law Group.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>The majority of Americans are personally affected by adoption. 6 in 10 Americans</strong> have had personal experience with adoption, meaning that they themselves, a family member, or a close friend was adopted, had adopted a child, or had placed a child for adoption.</em>\r\n<h3>Frequently Asked Questions Adoptions</h3>\r\n<strong>What is adoption?</strong>\r\n\r\nAdoption is the process of permanently placing a child into a family other than the family of the child’s birth. The parental rights and responsibilities of the biological parents cease and those rights and responsibilities are taken over by the adoptive parents. Once an adoption is completed, it is permanent.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is a Public Adoption?</strong>\r\n\r\nChildren in the public child welfare system are placed in permanent homes by public, government-operated agencies, or by private agencies contracted by a public agency to place waiting children. These types of adoptions involve children that have been placed in foster care by Child Protective Services or birth parents rights have been terminated.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is a Private Adoption?</strong>\r\n\r\nIn a private agency adoption, children are placed in non-relative homes through the services of a non-profit or for-profit agency which may be licensed by the State in which it operates. In an independent or non-agency adoption, children are placed in non-relative homes directly by the birth parents or through the services of one of the following: a licensed or unlicensed facilitator, certified medical doctor, member of the clergy, or attorney.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is the difference between an open adoption and a closed adoption?</strong>\r\n\r\nAn open adoption is when both sides of the adoption know some kind of identifying information about the other side. It can vary from case to case and there are many degrees of “openness”. It is up to the parties to reach an agreement on how much information, if any, will be shared. In a closed adoption, information about the two families involved is not shared between them. Medical history can be provided, however, all identifying information will be removed.\r\n\r\n<strong>In Step-Parent adoption are the birth parents rights terminated?</strong>\r\n\r\nNo. Step-parent adoptions occur when children are adopted by the spouse of one birth parent. The birth parent will be listed as a Petitioner in the suit.\r\n\r\n<strong>When can the mother of the baby start the adoption process?</strong>\r\n\r\nAs soon as she knows that she is pregnant.\r\n\r\n<strong>When does the Birth Mother actually sign the legal documents required for the adoption?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe law requires a waiting period after the delivery and depends on how the Birth Mother is feeling after her release from the hospital.\r\n\r\n<strong>Who takes the baby home from the hospital?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe baby goes directly from the hospital to the Adoptive Parent’s home.\r\n<h3>Resources to Help with Costs of Adopting:</h3>\r\n<h4>Federal Tax Credit**</h4>\r\nParents can claim a tax credit that covers adoption expenses. To take the credit or exclusion you will need to complete Form 8839, <em>Qualified Adoption Expenses</em>.\r\n\r\nAt the Website, of the Internal Revenue Service, you will find information about tax rules and changes to those rules. You can link to this site for information about the IRS Adoption Taxpayer Identification Number, and forPublication 968, on the Adoption Tax Credit and Tax Exclusion. (http://www.irs.ustreas.gov/)\r\n<h4>State Tax Credits**</h4>\r\nSeveral states have enacted state tax credits for families adopting children from the public child welfare system in that state.\r\n<h4>Adoption from the Foster Care System</h4>\r\nIf you are interested in adopting a child who is currently waiting in foster care, often not only are fees kept to a bare minimum or even waived, but many of the children will be eligible for federally-funded or state-funded adoption subsidy payments which help you meet the child’s ongoing needs. Some children qualify for Social Security Insurance payments or Medicaid coverage because of their medical conditions.\r\n<h4>Reimbursement for Non-Recurring Adoption Expense</h4>\r\nAfter families have finalized the adoption of a child with special needs from the public child welfare system, they may be able to apply for reimbursement of expenses they paid related to the adoption, which may include home study fees, travel expenses to meet the child, and attorney fees.\r\n<h4>Possible Employer Benefits</h4>\r\nMany employers provide a range of benefits for families who adopt including paid or unpaid leave when a child arrives in the home, reimbursement of some portion of adoption expenses, assistance with adoption information and referral services. Contact your human resource department for information about benefits available, if any.\r\n\r\n<em>**Contact a Certified Public Accountant for more tax information.</em>', 'Adoption', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '349-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 11:46:31', '2013-10-26 11:46:31', '', '349', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/349-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('460', '1', '2013-10-26 11:48:27', '2013-10-26 11:48:27', '<h3>Child Custody Modifications</h3>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/McbuiXEV0I0?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nNothing is more important to parents than their child. If you are involved in a child custody or visitation dispute in Denton, Tarrant or Wise County, Texas, we encourage you to schedule a consultation at Bowen Law Group\r\n\r\nIf you have been divorced and a parenting plan no longer serves the best interest of your children, you need experienced legal representation to handle your case. At Bowen Law Group, we offer experienced and dedicated legal services to people throughout Denton, Tarrant and Wise County. We take time to listen to clients, answer their questions and provide candid advice regarding their case. We are passionately defensive of clients’ parental rights and always pursue the best possible result in each case.\r\n<h3>Child Support Modifications</h3>\r\nDo you feel you are paying too much child support? Do you think you should be receiving more child support?\r\n\r\nIf you live in Denton or Wise County, Bowen Law Group can help. From our law offices in Denton, we represent clients in a wide range of family law matters, including child support modification proceedings.\r\n\r\nIf you choose to retain our firm for your case, we can perform a detailed child support calculation on your behalf, taking into account your income and the child support guidelines. In addition to handling child support modification proceedings for ex-spouses who have divorced, we represent unwed mothers and fathers who have been involved in paternity proceedings and are seeking to modify a previous child support order.\r\n\r\n<strong>Contact an Attorney</strong>\r\n\r\nTo speak with an attorney or schedule an appointment about a child custody or child support modification petition, contact Bowen Law Group.', 'Modifications', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '362-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 11:48:27', '2013-10-26 11:48:27', '', '362', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/362-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('461', '1', '2013-10-26 11:48:43', '2013-10-26 11:48:43', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Texas Lawyer for Child Custody Issues</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/yZJozOowRbU?rel=0\" height=\"338\" width=\"100%\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nFor many people, child custody issues can be the most intense and emotional aspect of family law in Texas. They can also be the most confusing ones to navigate. Although parents and caretakers often have good intentions, it can be hard for them to determine what kind of custody arrangements are best for their children. That is what makes it is so necessary for individuals and families to obtain advice from an experienced divorce attorney in Texas.\r\n<h3>Setting Up a Child Custody Plan</h3>\r\nTexas divorce law states that parents must create a parenting plan that outlines each parent’s rights and responsibilities toward their children. At Bowen Law Group in Denton, Texas, we help families navigate the complexities of the legal system and establish a custody and visitation plan that works for everyone involved. Our family law attorneys will work to help your family resolve its child custody issues as smoothly and efficiently as possible. Protecting the interests of our clients and their children is our primary goal. Contact us today in order to discuss your situation and learn how we can help.\r\n<h3>Making Child Custody Modifications</h3>\r\nSometimes, long after a divorce has been finalized and custody arrangements have been put in place, the needs of the family change and an existing court order must be modified. It can be necessary for a positive reason (such as a parent obtaining a new job), a negative one (such as an abusive parent) or something as simple as the changing schedule of an older child. The lawyers at Bowen Law Group provide assistance to families in Denton who need their custody agreements modified, including helping clients understand how child relocation laws impact any existing custody and visitation orders.\r\n<h3>Handling Adoptions</h3>\r\nDuring some divorce proceedings, it becomes clear that the children involved need to be placed with either stepparents or foster parents. In these situations, our law firm facilitates stepparent and foster parent adoptions by working with Child and Family Services (CFS) or Child Protective Services (CPS).  Attorney Chrysandra S. Bowen is responsible for bringing together all the necessary parties for adoption proceedings in Denton. Her extensive background in counseling and dedication to her clients makes her a superior advocate for families during these personal—and often delicate—legal proceedings.\r\n<h3>Contact Us</h3>\r\nIf you would like to speak with a lawyer about child custody or adoption, please contact our law office in Denton, Texas, at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, 7 days a week to ensure that you get answers to your most pressing legal questions right when you need them. Call us today!', 'Child Custody', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '350-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-26 11:48:43', '2013-10-26 11:48:43', '', '350', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/350-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
