INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('477', '1', '2013-10-29 11:30:11', '2013-10-29 11:30:11', '<em>“Brent has recently been my attorney, taking me to trial and winning. Trial lawyers are a special breed who think quickly on their feet and I can say without a doubt this guy is one of the best. If you\'re serious about winning, DO NOT LOOK ANY FURTHER!”</em> <strong>– J.R.</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>“Brent Bowen had my attention and confidence upon our first meeting. He was knowledgeable and kind and gave me the assurance I needed that my case was in the right hands. Thank you so much. I would use Attorney Bowen again.”</em> <strong>– A Criminal Defense Client</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>“Brent Bowen did a great job on my case. He handled my legal issues with professionalism and dignity, what helped to bring a case to successful result. I recommend Brent Bowen as your legal counselor.”</em><strong> - Alex</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>“Chrysandra and Nicole were awesome. I had to initiate court proceedings case twice in less than a year for custody of my child, but the outcome both times was great. The final result from the second case was better than expected. The entire firm has proven to be professional and dedicated to getting results.”</em> <strong>– A Child Custody Client</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>“I would highly recommend Brent Bowen to anyone who was in my position or needed to have a great lawyer. He definitely had my best interest in mind and was very informative throughout the whole process. I was recommended to him and I will defiantly be doing the same. Thanks for holding true to your word!”</em> <strong>- Jose</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>“Brent did a great job with keeping me informed and knowledgeable about the processes I was and would be going through. He gave me plenty of options and helped me weigh the pros and cons between each one. Overall he helped me get a result that I was pleased with and gave me a peace of mind throughout the time I was going through my legal issues.”</em> <strong>- Jordan</strong>', 'Testimonials', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '407-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-29 11:30:11', '2013-10-29 11:30:11', '', '407', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/407-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('478', '1', '2013-10-29 11:50:38', '2013-10-29 11:50:38', '<h2>Texas Law Firm Creating Smart Planning Solutions</h2>\r\n<p>According to some experts, two-thirds of Americans do not have an estate plan in place. Unfortunately, this may leave them or the people they care about in a difficult situation. At Bowen Law Group, we believe in smart planning for the future. Lawyers at our Denton, Texas, law firm help clients draft estate plans that protect the people they care about.</p>\r\n<p>Create an estate plan that protects the people you care about. Call [number type=\"1\"] to get started.</p>\r\n<h3>Estate Planning</h3>\r\n<h4>Denton Estate Planning Attorneys</h4>\r\n<p>Bowen Law Group, located in Denton County, provides advice and a variety of estate planning services for individuals. When assisting a client in drafting a will or trust, our estate planning Attorneys are sensitive to the impact our services will have on our client’s emotional and economic well-being. When helping a client with estate planning, Bowen Law Group, located in Denton County, works to achieve a solution that will effectively protect the client’s interests and ensure his or her intentions will be carried out. Estate Planning is a process that requires careful listening and thorough preparation and attention to detail, at Bowen Law Group our attorneys are committed to providing that quality of legal counsel.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Do you need a lawyer to write a will?</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you do not have a large estate, you may be considering drafting your own will, health care directive/living will/physician directive, and durable power of attorney, the documents that every adult should have in place. We urge you to reconsider. By preparing your own documents you run the chance of a document missing essential elements, leaving the estate at risk. If you would like to discuss your estate planning needs, please contact Bowen Law Groups Denton County Office. There is no charge for your initial consultation.</p>\r\n<h4>Our estate planning services</h4>\r\n<p>Our attorneys are prepared to assist clients with a full range of estate planning services:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Preparation of wills</li>\r\n<li>Preparation of living wills/health care directives</li>\r\n<li>Preparation of Powers of Attorney</li>\r\n<li>Drafting trusts, including testamentary trusts, trusts for minors, disability trusts, and living trusts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>An experienced wills and trusts lawyer should be able to advise you in all of your estate planning needs with the foresight and precision writing a will demands. From simple wills, living wills, testamentary trust wills and other estate planning tools, a Bowen Law Group wills and trusts attorney can help you make the decisions that will benefit your loved ones the most.**</p>\r\n<p><em>**We are Not Certified Professional Accountants, we advise you to allow us to consult with a CPA to protect your interests.</em></p>\r\n<p>When properly written, an estate plan gives your loved ones the legal protections they deserve and the guidance they need to make difficult decisions.</p>\r\n<p>An estate plan is more than just a will. A complete estate plan may include several documents, depending on your needs:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Wills</li>\r\n<li>Trusts</li>\r\n<li>Powers of attorney</li>\r\n<li>Advanced healthcare directives</li>\r\n<li>Guardianships or conservatorships</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Probate</h3>\r\n<p>Our law firm also guides clients through the Texas probate process. Probate and estate administration can often be time consuming and complex, but it is easier with the help of a knowledgeable lawyer who can answer your questions about how the law may apply in your case.</p>\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\n<p>To talk about estate planning or probate with an attorney at Bowen Law Group, please contact our Denton, Texas, law office at [number type=\"1\"]. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns — especially when you need them most.</p>\r\n', 'Estate Planning and Probate', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '292-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-29 11:50:38', '2013-10-29 11:50:38', '', '292', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/292-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('479', '1', '2013-10-29 11:51:41', '2013-10-29 11:51:41', '<h2>Frequently Asked Questions Estate Planning</h2>\r\n<p><strong>What does a Will do?</strong></p>\r\n<p>A will is a legal document that allows you to name a guardian for your child and specify who will inherit your property after you die. Without a will, you will have no say in what happens to your property.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is Probate?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Probate is the legal process an estate passes through to make sure property is distributed in accordance with a will or according to the laws of the state if there is no will.</p>\r\n<p><strong>How long does it take to Probate a Will?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The probate process usually takes about a year to complete as the validity of the will must be established.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is a Living Will?</strong></p>\r\n<p>A living will is a legal document that a person uses to make known his or her wishes regarding life prolonging medical treatments. It can also be referred to as an advance directive, health care directive, or a physician’s directive. A living will should not be confused with a living trust, which is a mechanism for holding and distributing a person’s assets to avoid probate.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is a Health Care Power of Attorney?</strong></p>\r\n<p>A Durable Power of Health Care Power of Attorney empowers a person you designate to make health-care decisions for you. Health care decisions include the power to consent, refuse consent or withdraw consent to any type of medical care, treatment, service or procedure.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is a Durable Power of Attorney?</strong></p>\r\n<p>A Durable Power of Attorney is an authorization to act on someone else’s behalf in a legal or business matter.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What does a Trust do?</strong></p>\r\n<p>A trust enables you to create a separate legal entity to protect your property and assets from probate, some taxes** and public scrutiny. Trusts may be established while you are living or upon your death as set forth in your will.</p>\r\n<p><em>**We are Not Certified Public Accountants, we advise you to allow us to consult with a CPA to protect your interests.</em></p>\r\n', 'Estate Planning FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '366-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-29 11:51:41', '2013-10-29 11:51:41', '', '366', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/366-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
