INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('590', '1', '2013-11-25 06:40:40', '2013-11-25 06:40:40', '<b>Interviewer: </b>How long does the mediation process generally take to resolve?\r\n\r\n<b>Chrysandra Bowen: </b>Mediation can be short, it can be long; it depends on what the issues of your case are.  If you are doing discovery, generally you are going to want to have some things prepared for mediation.  You don\'t want to go into mediation without having looked at all of your issues and either gotten supportive documentation or be as prepared almost as you would be for court, going to a contested matter.\r\n\r\nA case that has pretty much all the issues figured out and there is just maybe two major issues left at play such as child support or a piece of property, you will want all the documents that support your side. There needs to be time for discovery or the ability to speak with and actually get all of the information that you need in order to go into mediation to address all of your issues.\r\n\r\n<b>In Denton County, Mediation Typically Begins as an 8-Hour, One Day Session </b>\r\n\r\nMediation typically in Denton County, is a one day requirement that you are there from 9 to 5, you work all day, and you try to mediate the case.  If you have a private mediator, which are more expensive, and you use one when there is higher valued property at stake and the clients are high income earners then you are going to most likely use a private mediator and it works much the same way.  They can have you in the same room or they can have you in separate rooms and go back and forth.\r\n\r\n<b>With a Private Mediator, the Sessions Can Last for Several Days until an Agreement Is Reached </b>\r\n\r\nA private mediator can decide to mediate for however long they want.  The mediator is in control whether or not they call an impasse or not.  They can go up to several days if that is what is needed in order to get you to where you need to go.  All parties just have to agree to which form you are going to use.', 'How Long Can It Take to Arrive at a Resolution in Mediation? ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-long-can-it-take-to-arrive-at-a-resolution-in-mediation', '', '', '2013-11-25 06:59:48', '2013-11-25 06:59:48', '', '0', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/?page_id=590', '0', 'page', '', '0');
