u are going to use.', 'How Long Can It Take to Arrive at a Resolution in Mediation? ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '590-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-25 06:40:40', '2013-11-25 06:40:40', '', '590', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/590-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('592', '1', '2013-11-25 06:41:46', '2013-11-25 06:41:46', '<b>Interviewer: </b>What is enforcement and contempt?\r\n\r\n<b>Chrysandra Bowen: </b>Enforcement can be for property, it can be for child support, spousal maintenance or it can be for payments, for custody, it can be for a number of different issues.  There are certain actions underneath the family code where you can ask for jail time and that\'s more or less what is known as contemptive.\r\n\r\n<b>Contempt Is a Violation and Enforcement Is the Judge’s Ruling That a Party must abide by; Enforcement and Contempt Can Be Punishable with a Jail Sentence</b>\r\n\r\nContempt is being in violation of the court\'s order, so essentially you are set out to do these things.  You want the judge to enforce the matter, for example, child support.  You want the judge to enforce that they need to be paying it and then depending if they didn\'t pay it, then you can ask for jail time, you can ask for probation, you can ask for payments back, you can ask for attorney\'s fees.  That is what the enforcement and contempt is.  They are the same thing.\r\n\r\nYou can ask for the same thing inside one pleading for that and you can ask for several different things as long as you meet the requirements of the law.  Child support needs to be at least 30 days overdue in order to file an enforcement action.  Child custody issues arise when one parent does not have access to the children.\r\n\r\nYou can ask for enforcement of that and you have different options.  You don\'t have to necessarily say throw them in jail, you can say I want make up time or that there have been so many missed visitations that you can ask for custody of the children to revert to you.\r\n\r\nThere are different things that you can ask for.  If there was a piece of property that wasn\'t delivered, you can ask that the judge order that monetary value be paid to you in a certain matter, in a certain time frame.', 'Enforcement and Contempt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'enforcement-and-contempt', '', '', '2013-11-25 06:57:48', '2013-11-25 06:57:48', '', '0', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/?page_id=592', '0', 'page', '', '0');
