INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('598', '1', '2013-11-25 06:46:22', '2013-11-25 06:46:22', '<b>Chrysandra Bowen: </b>The most difficult cases are ones that involve a protective order.  Anything that involves a protective order is a difficult case because you are talking about allegations of harm to someone, whether it is the person that has been victimized or the person that is being accused of victimizing someone else. You are dealing with professionals.  You are dealing with experts.  You are dealing with medical issues.\r\n\r\nYou have to possess a wide range of understanding of not just the legal aspects but you are going to have to understand drugs and medications and if someone has been diagnosed with a particular disorder, you have to understand those.  Those are a lot more in depth cases.  They take a lot more time.\r\n\r\n<b>Protective Order Cases Are Time Intensive and Require a Thorough Knowledge of the Law </b>\r\n\r\nProtective order cases take time because there is so much more preparation and understanding and the case may hinge on your experts, your medical providers, or psychologists or counselors, and then neighbors or witnesses that have seen it, and police records.  They are just much more involved and you work with time constraints and the evidential rules so you are able to present evidence, that they can be a challenge.', 'Why Are Cases with Protective Orders Difficult for Attorneys?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-are-cases-with-protective-orders-difficult-for-attorneys', '', '', '2013-11-25 07:03:51', '2013-11-25 07:03:51', '', '0', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/?page_id=598', '0', 'page', '', '0');
