INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('600', '1', '2013-11-25 06:47:47', '2013-11-25 06:47:47', '<b>Interviewer: </b>How does Texas family law differ from everywhere else?\r\n\r\n<b>Chrysandra Bowen: </b>I mentioned that Texas law is different concerning late child support payments.  I actually have a case like that right now where I\'m dealing with another state and the order came from another state. The parties are all here, so we are trying to deal with that state because they require different things and they calculate interest completely different than we do.\r\n\r\nTexas factors in a percentage of the income earned by the parent paying child support.  In other states, it\'s they take both parent’s income into consideration and they arrive at a mathematical equation and come up with the number for child support.\r\n\r\n<b>Other States Do Not Add Interest to Late Child Support Payments</b>\r\n\r\nThe other states don\'t tack on interest for payments that aren\'t made.  Other states can ask for some state funding to be paid back. For example, a mother files for child support and files for state aide, like the WIC program or food stamps or Medicaid. If the state gave funds to that mother, other states can actually ask for that money to be paid by the parent that is ordered to be paying child support.\r\n\r\n<b>Texas Is a Community Property State</b>\r\n\r\nProperty issues are also different in other states.  In Texas, it\'s community property.  Other states have different allocations for separate or community property.  Texas, it is just straight across the board, either you are separate or it is community property.\r\n\r\n<b>Interviewer: </b>When someone is looking for a divorce lawyer or looking for someone to file a divorce or assist them with adoption, why would your firm be the right firm for that?\r\n\r\n<b>What Should You Look for When Considering Retaining a Family Law Attorney? A Good Family Law Attorney Is Empathetic, Caring and Possesses Good Listening Skills</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Chrysandra Bowen: </b>Whether that is a detriment to me or not, my cases affect me, too.\r\n\r\nFor the most part, an attorney can say, you know, I don\'t have to live with that and I get to close the door and walk off.  My cases involve drawing out what a client is feeling and maybe that is due to my counseling background.\r\n\r\nI\'m also not afraid to go to court.  I think that settling a case and negotiating is always the best option because you have control over that and it\'s not so emotional when you are able to settle it versus waiting.  The unknown is always scary for people and that\'s what court is.  Court is the unknown. At the end of the day, I have no problems going to court and moving the case along so that way we are not sitting out three years from now and we\'re going okay, well, we might want to set this for something.\r\n\r\nI having good listening skills and I look at the whole picture in a case versus just this is the one issue that the client originally came in with. By looking at the big picture, I can help clients get what they really need when a case is resolved.\r\n\r\n<b>Interviewer: </b>What would be the best way to contact you?\r\n\r\n<b>Chrysandra Bowen: </b>The best way to reach us is to call our main number, which is 940-566-0606.  The staff in the front of the office are generally are the ones that answer all of our initial calls.  They set you up to talk with me or they will set you up to talk with Brent, depending on what your issue is and what your needs are.\r\n\r\nThey can get some of the background that way and if it\'s a special issue, we can prepare in advance and we are ready to discuss the subject when you come in.  I know it streamlines that initial consultation.', 'Does Family Law in Texas Differ from Other States?  ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'does-family-law-in-texas-differ-from-other-states', '', '', '2013-11-25 06:56:59', '2013-11-25 06:56:59', '', '0', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/?page_id=600', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('601', '1', '2013-11-25 06:47:47', '2013-11-25 06:47:47', '<b>Interviewer: </b>How does Texas family law differ from everywhere else?\r\n\r\n<b>Chrysandra Bowen: </b>I mentioned that Texas law is different concerning late child support payments.  I actually have a case like that right now where I\'m dealing with another state and the order came from another state. The parties are all here, so we are trying to deal with that state because they require different things and they calculate interest completely different than we do.\r\n\r\nTexas factors in a percentage of the income earned by the parent paying child support.  In other states, it\'s they take both parent’s income into consideration and they arrive at a mathematical equation and come up with the number for child support.\r\n\r\n<b>Other States Do Not Add Interest to Late Child Support Payments</b>\r\n\r\nThe other states don\'t tack on interest for payments that aren\'t made.  Other states can ask for some state funding to be paid back. For example, a mother files for child support and files for state aide, like the WIC program or food stamps or Medicaid. If the state gave funds to that mother, other states can actually ask for that money to be paid by the parent that is ordered to be paying child support.\r\n\r\n<b>Texas Is a Community Property State</b>\r\n\r\nProperty issues are also different in other states.  In Texas, it\'s community property.  Other states have different allocations for separate or community property.  Texas, it is just straight across the board, either you are separate or it is community property.\r\n\r\n<b>Interviewer: </b>When someone is looking for a divorce lawyer or looking for someone to file a divorce or assist them with adoption, why would your firm be the right firm for that?\r\n\r\n<b>What Should You Look for When Considering Retaining a Family Law Attorney? A Good Family Law Attorney Is Empathetic, Caring and Possesses Good Listening Skills</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Chrysandra Bowen: </b>Whether that is a detriment to me or not, my cases affect me, too.\r\n\r\nFor the most part, an attorney can say, you know, I don\'t have to live with that and I get to close the door and walk off.  My cases involve drawing out what a client is feeling and maybe that is due to my counseling background.\r\n\r\nI\'m also not afraid to go to court.  I think that settling a case and negotiating is always the best option because you have control over that and it\'s not so emotional when you are able to settle it versus waiting.  The unknown is always scary for people and that\'s what court is.  Court is the unknown. At the end of the day, I have no problems going to court and moving the case along so that way we are not sitting out three years from now and we\'re going okay, well, we might want to set this for something.\r\n\r\nI having good listening skills and I look at the whole picture in a case versus just this is the one issue that the client originally came in with. By looking at the big picture, I can help clients get what they really need when a case is resolved.\r\n\r\n<b>Interviewer: </b>What would be the best way to contact you?\r\n\r\n<b>Chrysandra Bowen: </b>The best way to reach us is to call our main number, which is 940-566-0606.  The staff in the front of the office are generally are the ones that answer all of our initial calls.  They set you up to talk with me or they will set you up to talk with Brent, depending on what your issue is and what your needs are.\r\n\r\nThey can get some of the background that way and if it\'s a special issue, we can prepare in advance and we are ready to discuss the subject when you come in.  I know it streamlines that initial consultation.', 'Does Family Law in Texas Differ from Other States?  ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '600-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-25 06:47:47', '2013-11-25 06:47:47', '', '600', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/600-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
