INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('647', '1', '2014-01-30 10:32:46', '2014-01-30 10:32:46', '<b>Interviewer: </b>What about for people that you’re working with, that feel guilty for a crime, or they believe they’re guilty?  Do they throw themselves at the mercy of the court, or do they just fight the charges?\r\n\r\n<b>Always Go over Your Options with an Attorney</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Brent Bowen: </b>Most people know they’re guilty.  Most people don’t come to my office and say, “I never did this.  There’s no way.”  Maybe there’s no way to prove it, but it’s very rare they say, “I never did this.”   The bottom line is you want an attorney to explore all your options; to review the case.  The attorney will review if there is any legal way that you could get out of the case or at least minimize your exposure.\r\n\r\nI’ve had cases where, at the end of the day, we did a better investigation than the police did, and that resulted in the case being dismissed, because we outworked the police.  It doesn’t happen a lot, but it does happen.  It only happens, obviously, in the bigger cases; we’re talking burglary or sexual assault or robbery. With those charges, we’re going out and doing our own investigation, hiring our own private investigators to do the work.\r\n\r\nObviously, we tend to have better outcomes, because I don’t have to rely on the police.  I can go do my own investigation, and not rely on the police’s investigation I order to defend my clients.\r\n\r\n<b>Will Your Arrest and Criminal Charges become Public Information? </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Interviewer: </b>How public is someone’s situation going to be?  Are friends and family and work going to find out?\r\n\r\n<strong>The Information about an Arrest and Criminal Charges Are Likely to be Posted Online but Does Have to Be Researched</strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Brent Bowen: </b>In Denton County, there’s a Web site.  Many of our police departments have mug shots up there posted online.  It’s just a matter of someone Googling your name and they’ll be able to find out that you were in Denton County jail or Denton city jail.\r\n\r\n<strong>There are Companies That Post Mug Shot Photos and Charge Money to Remove Them</strong>\r\n\r\nThe biggest headache—and I don’t know how we’re going to get around this or deal with this in the future—is there are new companies that are capturing the mug shots off the city’s and county’s jail reports.  They’re basically demanding money to take your to take your picture down after they post it.\r\n\r\nIt is so difficult to prevent information about my clients from being posted that when I can do it, it’s a rarity.  I try to keep their information from being up for very long, so that these companies don’t capture it and then put it out on the Web, and then demand money to take it down.', 'Is It Ever Advisable to Plead Guilty and to Receive Mercy from the Court?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'is-it-ever-advisable-to-plead-guilty-and-to-receive-mercy-from-the-court', '', '', '2014-01-30 10:53:04', '2014-01-30 10:53:04', '', '0', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/?page_id=647', '0', 'page', '', '0');
