INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('765', '1', '2014-02-17 14:12:50', '2014-02-17 14:12:50', '<b><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-766\" alt=\"1197-Amanda Perry Hayes\" src=\"http://www.brentbowen.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/1197-Amanda-Perry-Hayes-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />Raleigh, N.C.</b> - 41-year-old Amanda Hayes is accused of first-degree murder in the death of her husband\'s ex-girlfriend, Laura Ackerson. Jurors in her murder trial saw surveillance photos of Amanda on Thursday which showed her dumping four cartons, containing seven unopened one-gallon bottles of muriatic acid, at the end of a cul-de-sac near the Richmond, Texas, home of her sister.\r\n\r\nThe murder took place on July 13, 2011, and the place where the body was found was just 2 miles from the spot where Hayes unloaded the acid. Ackerson\'s dismembered remains were found in a nearby creek in Texas. According to John T. Schneider, an officer with Fort Bend County Environmental Enforcement in Fort Bend County, Texas, the drop-off was made just after 10 a.m. on July 20, 2011. This was the last day of Haye\'s three-day trip with her husband Grant Hayes. Schneider recovered the photos from his department\'s camera.\r\n\r\nWitnesses were called in to testify against Hayes in the trial, including Raymond Boyer, an employee at a Home Depot store in Texas, who said that Grant Hayes bought four containers of muriatic acid on July 19, 2011. He insisted he had to remove the odor of a wild hog from a pig pen.\r\n\r\nAccording to Wake County prosecutors, Amanda Hayes told her sister that she killed 27-year-old Ackerson when they met in the Hayeses\' third-floor Raleigh apartment. She also told her sister that the couple then cut up her body and dumped it in the creek six days later.\r\n\r\nAckerson\'s remains were collected for an autopsy which shows that she died of \" undetermined homicidal violence.\" The autopsy report also showed that she had a sharp puncture wound to the fourth cervical vertebra of the spine as well as crushed thyroid cartilage that was consistent with some type of asphyxia or blunt force trauma to the neck.\r\n\r\nDespite the availability of proof and photos, the defense attorneys insisted that their client had no knowledge of Ackerson\'s death. She later confessed when she found out about it because her husband had threatened to kill her.\r\n\r\n34-year-old Grant Hayes was convicted of first-degree murder in September. She is serving life in prison without the possibility of parole.\r\n\r\n<strong>News Source:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.wral.com/photos-show-amanda-hayes-dumping-acid-near-texas-crime-scene/13365467/\" target=\"_blank\">www.WRAL.com</a>', 'Hayes accused of first-degree murder after photos confirm dumping of acid near crime scene', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hayes-accused-of-first-degree-murder-after-photos-confirm-dumping-of-acid-near-crime-scene', '', '', '2014-02-17 14:12:50', '2014-02-17 14:12:50', '', '0', 'http://www.brentbowen.com/?p=765', '0', 'post', '', '0');
